<li>Sartorelli, Joseph J., 1994, &ldquo;Ruse on Gay Rights and
Affirmative Action,&rdquo; <em>Analysis</em>, 54 (April):
84&ndash;91.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1997, &ldquo;The Nature of Affirmative
Action, Anti-Gay Oppression, and the Alleviation of Enduring
Harm,&rdquo; <em>International Journal of Applied Philosophy</em>, 11
(Winter-Spring): 23&ndash;30.</li>

<li>Schmidt, Peter, 2008, &ldquo;Scholars Mount Sweeping Effort to
Measure Affirmative Action in Higher Education,&rdquo; <em>Chronicle
of Higher Education</em>, 54 (January 19): A19.</li>

<li>Schmill, Stu, 2022, &ldquo;We are reinstating our SAT/ACT
requirement for future admissions cycles,&rdquo; MIT
 [<a href="https://mitadmissions.org/blogs/entry/we-are-reinstating-our-sat-act-requirement-for-future-admissions-cycles/" target="other">available online</a>]</li>
 
<li>Segev, Re&rsquo;em, 2019, &ldquo;Affirmative Action: Well-Being,
justice, and Qualifications,&rdquo; <em>Ratio Juris</em>, 32 (June):
138&ndash;156.</li>

<li>Shelby, Tommie, 2014, &ldquo;Integration, Inequality, and
Imperatives of Justice: A Review Essay,&rdquo; <em>Philosophy &amp;
Public Affairs</em>, 42 (Summer): 253&ndash;285.</li>

<li>Sher, George, 1975, &ldquo;Justifying Reverse Discrimination in
Employment,&rdquo; <em>Philosophy &amp; Public Affairs</em>, 4
(Winter): 159&ndash;170.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1979, &ldquo;Reverse Discrimination, the
Future, and the Past,&rdquo; <em>Ethics</em>, 90 (October):
81&ndash;87.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1997, <em>Approximate Justice: Studies in
Non-Ideal Theory</em>, Lanham, Maryland: Rowman &amp;
Littlefield.</li>

<li>Shiner, Roger, 1973, &ldquo;Individuals, Groups and Inverse
Discrimination,&rdquo; <em>Analysis</em>, 33 (June):
185&ndash;187.</li>

<li>Silvestri, Philip, 1973, &ldquo;The Justification of Inverse
Discrimination,&rdquo; <em>Analysis</em>, 34 (October): 31.</li>

<li>Simon, Robert L., 1974, &ldquo;Preferential Hiring: A Reply to
Judith Jarvis Thomson,&rdquo; <em>Philosophy &amp; Public
Affairs</em>, 3 (Spring): 312&ndash;320.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1978, &ldquo;Statistical Justification of
Discrimination,&rdquo; <em>Analysis</em>, 38 (January):
37&ndash;42.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1979, &ldquo;Individual Rights and
&lsquo;Benign&rsquo; Discrimination,&rdquo; <em>Ethics</em>, 90
(October): 88&ndash;97.</li>

<li>Skrentny, John David, 1996, <em>The Ironies of Affirmative Action:
Politics, Culture, and Justice in America</em>, Chicago: University of
Chicago Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash; (ed.), 2001, <em>Color Lines: Affirmative
Action, Immigration, and Civil Rights Options for America</em>,
Chicago: University of Chicago Press.</li>

<li>Smyth, Frederick L. and John J. McArdle, 2004, &ldquo;Ethnic and
Gender Differences in Science Graduation at Selective Colleges with
Implications for Admission Policy and College Choice,&rdquo;
<em>Research in Higher Education</em>, 45 (June): 353&ndash;381.</li>

<li>Social and Organizational Psychologists, 2015: Brief in Support of
Respondents in Fisher v. University of Texas, 136 S. Ct. 2198
(2016):1&ndash;44.</li>

<li>Sowell, Thomas, 2004, <em>Affirmative Action Around the World: An
Empirical Study</em>, New Haven, Connecticut: Yale University Press.
[Reviewed by Carl Cohen in <em>Commentary</em>, 117 (April 2004):
73&ndash;76, and by Bernard Boxill in <em>Ethics &amp; International
Affairs</em>, 18: 114&ndash;115).</li>

<li>Stark, Susan, 2004, &ldquo;Taking Responsibility for Oppression:
Affirmative Action and Racial Injustice,&rdquo; <em>Public Affairs
Quarterly</em>, 18 (July): 205&ndash;221.</li>

<li>Steiner, Hillel, 1987, &ldquo;Capitalism, Justice and Equal
Starts,&rdquo; <em>Social Philosophy &amp; Policy</em>, 5:
49&ndash;71.</li>

<li>Sterba, James P., 2003, &ldquo;Defending Affirmative Action,
Defending Preferences,&rdquo; <em>Journal of Social Philosophy</em>,
34 (June): 285&ndash;300.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2004, &ldquo;The Michigan Cases and
Furthering the Justification of Affirmative Action,&rdquo;
<em>International Journal of Applied Philosophy</em>, 18 (1):
1&ndash;12.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2009, <em>Affirmative Action for the
Future</em>, Ithaca, New York: Cornell University Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2011, &ldquo;Responses to Allen, Appiah,
and Lawson,&rdquo; <em>Journal of Ethics</em>, 15 (September):
291&ndash;306.</li>

<li>Strasser, Mark, 2010, &ldquo;On Disguises, Tokens, and Affirmative
Action Policies,&rdquo; <em>Indiana Law Journal</em>, 85 (Fall):
1293&ndash;1301.</li>

<li>Stroud, Sarah, 1999, &ldquo;The Aim of Affirmative Action,&rdquo;
<em>Social Theory and Practice</em>, 25 (Fall): 385&ndash;408.</li>

<li>Stroup, Timothy, 1982, &ldquo;Affirmative Action and the
Police,&rdquo; <em>International Journal of Applied Philosophy</em>, 1
(Fall): 1&ndash;19.</li>

<li>Sturm, Susan and Lani Guinier, 1996, &ldquo;The Future of
Affirmative Action: Reclaiming an Innovative Ideal,&rdquo;
<em>California Law Review</em>, 84 (July): 953&ndash;1036.</li>

<li>Suk, Julie, 2017, &ldquo;Discrimination and Affirmative
Action,&rdquo; in Kasper Lippert-Rasmussen (ed.), <em>The Routledge
Handbook of the Ethics of Discrimination</em>, New York: Routledge,
pp. 394&ndash;406.</li>

<li>Sumner, L. W., 1987, &ldquo;Positive Sexism,&rdquo; <em>Social
Philosophy &amp; Policy</em>, 5: 204&ndash;222.</li>

<li>Symposium, 1979, &ldquo;<em>Bakke</em>&mdash;Civil Rights
Perspectives,&rdquo; <em>Harvard Civil Rights-Civil Liberties Law
Review</em>, 14 (Spring).</li>

<li>Symposium, 1996a, &ldquo;Race-Based Remedies,&rdquo;
<em>California Law Review</em>, 84 (July).</li>

<li>Symposium, 1996b, &ldquo;The Meanings of Merit&mdash;Affirmative
Action and the California Civil Rights Initiative,&rdquo; <em>Hastings
Constitutional Law Quarterly</em>, 23 (Summer).</li>

<li>Syverud, Kent D., 1999, Expert Report: <em>Grutter v.
Bollinger</em>, <em>Michigan Journal of Race and Law</em>, 5 (Fall):
451&ndash;454.</li>

<li>Tam, Mo Yin S. and Gilbert W. Bassett, Jr., 2004, &ldquo;Does
Diversity Matter? Measuring the Impact of High School Diversity on
Freshman GPA,&rdquo; <em>Policy Studies Journal</em>, 32:
129&ndash;144.</li>

<li>Taylor, Paul, 1973, &ldquo;Reverse Discrimination and Compensatory
Justice,&rdquo; <em>Analysis</em>, 33 (June): 177&ndash;182.</li>

<li>Taylor, Robert S., 2009, &ldquo;Rawlsian Affirmative
Action,&rdquo; <em>Ethics</em>, 119 (April): 476&ndash;506.</li>

<li>Thernstrom, Stephan and Abigail Thernstrom, 1997, <em>America in
Black and White: One Nation, Indivisible</em>, New York: Simon and
Schuster.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1999, &ldquo;Reflections on The Shape of
the River,&rdquo; <em>UCLA Law Review</em>, 46 (June):
1583&ndash;1631.</li>

<li>Thomas, Laurence, 2004, &ldquo;Equality and the Mantra of
Diversity,&rdquo; <em>University of Cincinnati Law Review</em>, 72:
931&ndash;965.</li>

<li>Thomson, Judith Jarvis, 1973, &ldquo;Preferential Hiring,&rdquo;
<em>Philosophy &amp; Public Affairs</em>, 2 (Summer):
364&ndash;384.</li>

<li>Tushnet, Mark, 1991, &ldquo;Change and Continuity in the Concept
of Civil Rights: Thurgood Marshall and Affirmative Action,&rdquo;
<em>Social Philosophy and Policy</em>, 8 (Spring): 150&ndash;171.</li>

<li>University of Texas, October 2015: Brief for Respondents,
