385&ndash;389.</li>

<li>Warnke, Georgia, 1998, &ldquo;Affirmative Action, Neutrality, and
Integration,&rdquo; <em>Journal of Social Philosophy</em>, 29
(Winter): 87&ndash;103.</li>

<li>Warren, Mary Anne, 1977, &ldquo;Secondary Sexism and Quota
Hiring,&rdquo; <em>Philosophy &amp; Public Affairs</em>, 6 (Spring):
240&ndash;261.</li>

<li>Washington, Tanya, 2004, &ldquo;The Diversity Dichotomy: The
Supreme Court&rsquo;s Reticence to Give a Capital R,&rdquo;
<em>University of Cincinnati Law Review</em>, 72: 977&ndash;1009.</li>

<li>Wasserstrom, Richard, 1976, &ldquo;Racism, Sexism, and
Preferential Treatment: An Approach to the Topics,&rdquo; <em>UCLA Law
Review</em>, 24 (February): 581&ndash;622.</li>

<li>West&ndash;Faulcon, Kimberly, 2017, &ldquo;Obscuring Asian Penalty
with Illusions of Black Bonus,&rdquo; <em>UCLA Law Review</em>, 64:
590&ndash;645.</li>

<li>Westmoreland, Robert, 2004, &ldquo;A New and Improved Affirmative
Action,&rdquo; <em>University of Cincinnati Law Review</em>, 72:
909&ndash;929.</li>

