<div id="other-internet-resources">

<h2 id="Oth">Other Internet Resources</h2>

<ul>

 <li><a href="http://www.usccr.gov/" target="other">United States Commission on Civil Rights</a></li>
 
 <li><a href="https://www.aaaed.org/aaaed/default.asp" target="other">American Association for Access, Equity and Diversity</a>,
 provides a resource page with many links to organizations mostly
supporting affirmative action</li>

 <li><a href="https://www.justice.gov/crt/appellate-section-affirmative-action" target="other">U.S. Department of Justice, Civil Rights Division</a>,
 contains briefs by the Department of Justice in many cases involving
affirmative action</li>

 <li><a href="https://www.americanbar.org/groups/diversity/resources/affirmative-action-resources/" target="other">American Bar Association</a>,
 contains briefs and articles representing the views of the ABA</li>

 <li><a href="https://americanallianceforequalrights.org/" target="other">American Alliance for Equal Rights</a>,
 founded by Edward Blum, the leading figure behind Students for Fair
Admissions</li>

 <li><a href="https://pacificlegal.org/blog/" target="other">Pacific Legal Foundation</a>,
 a conservative organization that litigates against affirmative
action</li>
</ul>
</div>

